title: For Sale:  Cobb MCR 200 in .308
postcontent:
Negotiable and willing to meet in person in public area. “Like new” Cobb MCR 200 chambered in 7.62 NATO. This rifle has a 24-inch Lothar Walther Barrel with 1:10 twist. This rifle utilizes the economical HK G3 magazines that can be purchased for less than $5.00 from Midway USA. MCR stands for Multi-Caliber-Rifle and it is built on the AR type design. MCR Semi-Automatic rifles come in four different models which interchange with each other from one series to the next. To change calibers for example from a .223 (MCR100) to .308 (MCR200) you simply change the upper receiver and magazine module. To change calibers on the same series rifle from one caliber to another within the same series for example, on an MCR400 from 300 Winchester Magnum to 338 Lapua Magnum you simply change out the barrel and bolt.  Made in Dallas, Geogia U.S.A. 
MCR Series Rifle Specifications:
-Upper/Lower receivers and magazine module made out of T6-6061aircraft aluminum.
-Semi-Automatic AR type gas operation.
-Free floated Lothar Walther barrel available in different lengths.
-M1913 rail machined on the upper receiver.
-AR type pistol grip and butt stock.
-AR type trigger group parts that interchange with standard AR's.
-Rifle weight depending on calibers from 7 lbs to 16 lbs.

title: For Sale:  Gun Prices
postcontent: Had to put up this post after looking for an item and finding out there are so many people posting ridiculous prices on their used weapons and gear.  There are so many listings asking above retail price on used items.  Folks......a Glock 43 can be had at $500 out the door.  Current price on a Glock G42 is $445 out the door tax and background included.   You can shave $20 off of that on GB.  Yes even with shipping and transfer.  Look, just because you bought your Sig, Glock, or whatever at Joes massive retail shop and paid too much does not mean anyone wants to pay more than retail and absorb your loss.  And if you added a bunch of add ons you probably won't get what you want for the item adding in the upgrades.  Gotta be real here.  Doesn't matter how much chrome you add to an Ultra Glide the price is still the same on the market.  Most times people don't even want those upgrades so now it is worth less.  Unless they are good optics or laser etc.  Upgraded mag catches, etc. is what I am referring to. So, Please check the market.  Look around at GB etc.  Post something you are going to sell.  One fellow said after listing it he had changed his mind.  Don't waste everyones time listing the thing unless you absolutely want to sell it at a fair market value.  Most of all, drop the attitude when someone informs you you are $75 bucks over what we can buy a new one for.  Don't get mad at legitimate buyers just because you paid too much and they are now the bearer of bad news.  And thank you to all of the sellers who post reasonable prices and have a great attitude as well.I have had dozens and dozens of responses saying thank you for the post.  I appreciate the responses.  One reader brought up a real point I thought worth mentioning.  When you sell it please close down the post.  He was right on target.  Thanks to everyone for the positive feedback.

title: For Sale:  Armslist Gun Prices
postcontent: Had to put up this post after looking for an item and finding out there are so many people posting ridiculous prices on their used weapons and gear.  There are so many listings asking above retail price on used items.  Folks......a Glock 43 can be had at $500 out the door.  Current price on a Glock G42 is $445 out the door tax and background included.   You can shave $20 off of that on GB.  Yes even with shipping and transfer.  Look, just because you bought your Sig, Glock, or whatever at Joes massive retail shop and paid too much does not mean anyone wants to pay more than retail and absorb your loss.  And if you added a bunch of add ons you probably won't get what you want for the item adding in the upgrades.  Gotta be real here.  Doesn't matter how much chrome you add to an Ultra Glide the price is still the same on the market.  Most times people don't even want those upgrades so now it is worth less.  Unless they are good optics or laser etc.  Upgraded mag catches, etc. is what I am referring to.  So, Please check the market.  Look around at GB etc.  Post something you are going to sell.  One fellow said after listing it he had changed his mind.  Don't waste everyones time listing the thing if you absolutely want to sell it at a fair market value.  Most of all, drop the attitude when someone informs you you are $75 bucks over what we can buy a new one for.  Don't get mad at legitimate buyers just because you paid too much and they are now the bearer of bad news.  And thank you to all of the sellers who post reasonable prices and have a great attitude as well.

title: For Sale:  AL Prices
postcontent: Had to put up this post after looking for an item and finding out there are so many people posting ridiculous prices on their used weapons and gear.  There are so many listings asking above retail price on used items.  Folks......a Glock 43 can be had at $500 out the door.  Current price on a Glock G42 is $445 out the door tax and background included.   You can shave $20 off of that on GB.  Yes even with shipping and transfer.  Look, just because you bought your Sig, Glock, or whatever at Joes massive retail shop and paid too much does not mean anyone wants to pay more than retail and absorb your loss.  And if you added a bunch of add ons you probably won't get what you want for the item adding in the upgrades.  Gotta be real here.  Doesn't matter how much chrome you add to an Ultra Glide the price is still the same on the market.  Most times people don't even want those upgrades so now it is worth less.  Unless they are good optics or laser etc.  Upgraded mag catches, etc. is what I am referring to. So, Please check the market.  Look around at GB etc.  Post something you are going to sell.  One fellow said after listing it he had changed his mind.  Don't waste everyones time listing the thing if you absolutely want to sell it at a fair market value.  Most of all, drop the attitude when someone informs you you are $75 bucks over what we can buy a new one for.  Don't get mad at legitimate buyers just because you paid too much and they are now the bearer of bad news.  And thank you to all of the sellers who post reasonable prices and have a great attitude as well.
